   <text>
      <pb n="11"/>
      <body>
         <head>To <persName>
                    <ptr target="../persons/pers0311">Mrs. Burgoyne</ptr>
                </persName>
                <note place="foot" n="1">No details about <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0311">Mrs. Burgoyne</ptr>
                    </persName> have been discovered.</note>
            </head>
         <opener>
            <placeName>
                    <region>London</region>
                </placeName>
            <lb/>
            <date when="1756-0207">February 7, 1756</date>
            <lb/>
            <lb/>
         </opener>
         <p>If the estate is in the hands of an attorney it is not likely that you should recover anything of it. You have then only to say, 'The Lord gave, and the Lord hath taken away.'<note place="foot" n="2">
                    <index indexName="biblical">
                        <term cRef="Job1:21">Job 1:21</term>
                    </index>.</note> It seems God is now teaching you <seg ana="self-resignation">the great lesson of giving yourself up, soul and body, into his hands</seg>. And he has never failed and never will fail them that put their trust in him.<note place="foot" n="3">
                    <index indexName="biblical">
                        <term cRef="Ps18:30(BCP)">See Ps. 18:30 (BCP)</term>
                    </index>, etc.</note>
            </p>
         <p>Acquaint yourself with him, and you will be at <seg ana="peace">peace</seg>,<note place="foot" n="4">See Job 22:21.</note> even when the waves and storms go over you.<note place="foot" n="5">
                    <index indexName="biblical">
                        <term cRef="Ps42:9(BCP)">See Ps. 42:9 (BCP).</term>
                    </index>
                </note> <seg ana="suffering">Suffer all things for his sake who suffered more for you.</seg> And whenever you want help, ask and it shall be given you.<note place="foot" n="6">
                    <index indexName="biblical">
                        <term cRef="Matt7:7">Matt. 7:7</term>
                    </index>.</note>
            </p>
         <closer>I am,
            <signed>Your affectionate brother,<lb/>
               <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0001">John Wesley</ptr>
                    </persName>
            </signed>
         </closer>
      </body>
